RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 51. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LAGRUE rated from outside on the backstretch, vied for the lead four wide when allowed on the bend, was all out in the lane and edged ahead in time. BLUE TEARDROPS was sent to vie for the early lead between rivals, two wide through the turn, fought gamely in the stretch but had to settle for second best. MY KINDA TETON prominent from inside on the backstretch, was outrun and forced to wait for room on the bend, got through along the rail approaching the quarter pole, battled for the lead but could not sustain his bid in the waning yards. UNCLE O. G. exchanged bumps with LORD SHAFTESBURY at the break, disputed the pace just outside BLUE TEARDROPS, was caught in tight quarters between rivals leaving the quarter pole, retreated a bit then flattened out for the drive. LORD SHAFTESBURY exchanged bumps with UNCLE O. G., soon dropped well back from the rest and lacked a significant stretch response.

ENTRY.NAME: My Kinda Teton
ENTRY.COMMENT: got thru inside 1/4, vied, weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: Blue Teardrops
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent to lead, 2 wide turn, dueled thru stretch, game effort

ENTRY.NAME: Lord Shaftesbury
ENTRY.COMMENT: exchanged bumps start, saved ground, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Uncle O. G.
ENTRY.COMMENT: exchanged bumps start, 3 wide speed, flattened out stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Lagrue
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated outside, let out 4 wide turn, all out stretch, edged ahead

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 59. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 20 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FUTURE VISION shared the early lead between rivals, was roused two wide on the bend, drew off under urging inside the final furlong and was kept to task to the waning yards. WINDIGO SPIRIT bumped a time or two with SAFE at the start, disputed the pace inside horses, gained the rail into the turn, was no match for FUTURE VISION inside the last eighth, began to wear down late but lasted for second. SAFE bumped with WINDIGO SPIRIT at the break, had the inside early on, angled out for a clear path into the bend, came into the lane from path four, altered in some when he lost his path midstretch, took over third inside the final sixteenth and was closing in on WINDIGO SPIRIT nearing the wire. STAY STRONG settled just off the inside, also swung out into the turn, lost further ground widest entering the stretch, showed a willingness to run late and narrowly missed third. HE'S A FINE MAN contested the pace from outside, took the bend three wide, began to yield, drifted out some midstretch and continued to gradually give way. BRASKA moved toward the outside early on, lost ground on the turn, angled in some into the lane and lacked a significant response under hand urging.

ENTRY.NAME: Braska
ENTRY.COMMENT: showed little

ENTRY.NAME: Stay Strong
ENTRY.COMMENT: angled out turn, 5-path stretch bid, closing

ENTRY.NAME: Safe
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, 4-path turn, altered in stretch, gaining

ENTRY.NAME: Windigo Spirit
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, inside turn, no match for winner, weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: Future Vision
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied between, roused turn, drew off last 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: He's a Fine Man
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied outside, 3 wide turn, weakened stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 3 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IRISH DECLARATION rated from inside, commenced his bid after a half mile, took over with two furlongs to go then steadily opened up under mild urging in the lane. WILLOW RIDGE rated toward the outside, picked up his pace three wide on the second turn, fanned out further for the drive, took over second, was all out and proved easily best of the others. READY REDDING broke on top, was soon chasing MADE TO FIT from just off the rail, went for the lead between rivals on the second bend, found himself boxed in nearing the quarter pole, altered in entering the stretch, was not match for the top pair but lasted for the show. FRONTANA was settled well back and well off the inside, picked up his pace after a half mile, lost ground widest through the second turn, passed outside tired ones the final furlong and was closing in on READY REDDING late. SHOBIZ STAR chased from outside, came into contention four wide on the second turn, swung outside WILLOW RIDGE for the stretch run and gave way. MADE TO FIT soon had a clear lead, showed the way along or just off the inside, began to wear down on the second turn, was overtaken from inside with a quarter mile left, floated out some for the drive and steadily faded. AMERICAN SUCCESS showed little in a ground-saving trip.

ENTRY.NAME: Irish Declaration
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated inside, roused 1/2, much the best, mild drive

ENTRY.NAME: Made to Fit
ENTRY.COMMENT: sprinted clear, 2-3 path 2nd turn, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: American Success
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, showed little

ENTRY.NAME: Frontana
ENTRY.COMMENT: well back early, lost ground, mild bid

ENTRY.NAME: Ready Redding
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3 path, angled in into stretch, flattened out

ENTRY.NAME: Shobiz Star
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle move outside, gave way 5 wide stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Willow Ridge
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3-4 wide, bid 2nd turn, all out stretch, easily 2nd best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Special Weight Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THAT'S A BIRD, unruly in the gate, popped his gate door open, was contained well by the assistant starter, stalked the early speed from outside once his gate was closed and the race began, commenced her bid after two furlongs, advanced four wide on the bend, lugged in slightly as she responded to urging upper stretch then drew away from the rest while ridden out inside the final eighth. THERE RUNS MARY hesitated at the break, quickly recovered, advanced between rivals, took the lead after two furlongs, had the rail on the turn, was no match for THAT'S A BIRD the last furlong but stayed clear for the place. MO WANNA GO soon took the advantage from inside, lost the lead after a quarter mile, was two wide taking the bend, ran evenly through the stretch but was unchallenged for third. MADELYN ATTACK prominent between rivals, was three wide through the turn, altered out some when THAT'S A BIRD took her path upper stretch and failed to have a serious late bid. GABRIELLA ATTACK was an early contender along the rail but steadily yielded after two furlongs.

ENTRY.NAME: Gabriella Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: steadily faded inside

ENTRY.NAME: Mo Wanna Go
ENTRY.COMMENT: early speed inside, 2 wide turn, evenly stretch

ENTRY.NAME: There Runs Mary
ENTRY.COMMENT: hesitated, inside turn, no match for winner stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Madelyn Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3 wide turn, angled out upper stretch, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: That's a Bird
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked outside, let out 4 wide turn, drew away last 1/8

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Maxim M. Jakovac & Susan J. Jakovac

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 55. Claiming Purse 9500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AH LEAH prompted the pace from between horses, was roused three wide on the bend, fanned five wide entering the lane, altered outside BEIRUT BEAUTY upper stretch, rallied under steady urging and caught BOBBIE TOO TOO near the wire. BOBBIE TOO TOO broke alertly, set a pressured pace between horses, was challenged from outside on the turn, floated out some into the stretch, moved clear of the rest but began to wear down inside the final sixteenth. BEIRUT BEAUTY pressed the early speed from outside, went for the lead from path three on the bend, did not stay with BOBBIE TOO TOO into the lane, drifted out some upper stretch, held a straight path the last furlong and closed the gap belatedly in the waning yards. TEMPLUNA settled well off the early pace, picked up her pace from inside leaving the turn, waited for room upper stretch, got through along the rail with a furlong to go, closed well but was too late. SUPERTRIX was away somewhat slowly, stayed well off the inside on the backstretch and through the bend, came into the lane from the middle of the track, surged the last eighth but was also too late. ABBMAR boxed in behind BOBBIE TOO TOO on the backstretch, was shuffled back into the turn, angled out four wide, lost further ground staying outside AH LEAH into the lane and upper stretch and rallied belatedly the final furlong as well. TWO MORE TIMES was steadied behind traffic leaving the chute, settled inside, picked up her pace some just off the rail on the bend, lost ground when swung out behind ABBMAR entering the stretch, angled in some for a clear path between horses approaching the eighth pole and also showed a willingness to run deep stretch. SWEET JUSTICE well placed from inside, gave way for the drive. GHAALEB'S DOMAIN prominent two wide on the backstretch, began to quickly fade nearing the end of a half mile.

ENTRY.COMMENT: inside, gave way stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 66. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 23500. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING 10,000 FOR HORSES THAT HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 20 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOON PIES IMAGE rated just off the early pace, went for the lead three wide on the bend, battled through the lane and edged ahead nearing the wire. CANTOO vied for the lead between horses from the beginning, was two wide through the turn, fought gamely in the stretch, did not have enough left in the waning yards but was clearly second best. JULYNNE prominent between rivals, was two wide on the bend, swung outside MOON PIES IMAGE entering the lane, gained third inside the final furlong but could only just hold her position late. GHAALEB'S RANGER a step slow at the break, was boxed in on the backstretch and through the turn, gradually altered outside MOON PIES IMAGE in the stretch and failed to have the needed late kick. PRIMITY was hustled to contest the pace from inside on the backstretch but began to wear down before finishing a half mile.

ENTRY.COMMENT: boxed in early, angled out 4 wide stretch, weakened stretch

ENTRY.COMMENT: used early inside

ENTRY.COMMENT: 2 wide speed, dueled stretch, gamely

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 7 1M Dirt CR: 90. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 19000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 20 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIAMOND DAVE jostled briefly with ALLEN at the break, was settled inside, picked up his pace after a half mile, came into contention under urging three wide on the second bend, quickly moved clear upper stretch and maintained full control while with little asking inside the final sixteenth. EVERLOVINGHAND broke inward, bumping YOU'RE IN COREY, was four wide as he vied for the lead between rivals leaving the first turn, did not stay with BABA'S BOY after a half mile, lost considerable ground, staying outside the latter leaving the second turn and upper stretch, took over second inside the last eighth and held his position under steady handling. MKAR THE FAST settled outside, also commenced his bid after a half mile, lost ground four wide on the second bend, was forced out leaving that turn to be in path ten into the lane, jostled briefly with ALLEN and found best stride too late deep stretch. BABA'S BOY lost ground as he advanced five then four wide through the first turn, moved clear and gradually angled to the inside after four furlongs, drifted out badly leaving the second turn and entering the lane and gradually yielded. ALLEN jostled briefly with DIAMOND DAVE at the start, was settled off the inside, also commenced his bid after a half mile, followed the latter on the second bend, fanned out trying to gain a clear path leaving that turn, forced to path nine into the stretch, jostled briefly between YOU'RE IN COREY and MKAR THE FAST once straightened for the drive and lacked a significant late response. YOU'RE IN COREY bumped at the break, was hustled along to stay close between rivals, improved position three then four wide on the second turn, was also forced out leaving that bend, altered out a bit further for a clear path outside EVERLOVINGHAND upper stretch, jostled briefly with ALLEN and faded. VIOLENZA D'ORO was a brief factor from inside but began to fade after two furlongs. BLAZEN ROAD displayed early speed along or just off the rail and steadily gave way two wide before finishing six furlongs.
